04/02/2007
BRCKO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Brcko District's international supervisor, Raffi Gregorian, issued four decrees on Friday (February 2nd), aimed at speeding up the reform processes and the resolution of lagging administrative problems. 
Gregorian set a deadline of February 9th for the mayor of Brcko to form special task forces to update district laws. 
He also appointed Goran Lujic as the district's new police chief, filling a post that has been vacant for over five months. 
(Nezavisne novine - 03/02/07; OHR Sources - 02/02/07)
